Question: Would you rather go to a music festival, have fun and sleep in a tent, or stay home, watch TV series and have some tasty snacks?
Answer: I’m learning to stop looking for happiness. People love to sell you this idea that once you achieve this, once you get that, once this happens, you will be ✨ happy ✨and the reason you’re not happy right now is because you don’t have these things that you’re chasing. But there is no pinnacle of life that you reach and then suddenly you’re immune to being sad and bad things don’t happen to you anymore. Life is hard. Life is sad. The world is deeply imperfect and unfair. And that is not going to change. Instead of looking for this before and after life where once you reach the after, you’re “happy”, I’m learning that fulfillment and a real sense of joy is found in the everyday and it is found in love. Not just the finding your soulmate type of love, but sacrificial love. The type of love you don’t just feel, but you practice. When you live your life for something greater than yourself. When your actions are all centered around bringing love to those around you. When loving yourself isn’t the end goal, but a necessary means for you to be able to love others more fully. When the goal of your life is to be happy, you will constantly be disappointed because happiness is a feeling that comes and goes. When the goal of your life is to love, you can attain that goal everyday regardless of what people do to you, how hard things are, or even if everything is falling apart, because the times it is hardest to love are the times when your love means the most. We as human beings were simply designed to give and receive love and when we are doing that is when we truly feel fulfilled, grounded, and alive ❤️

Question: How do you deal with stressful situations?
Answer:
1. Take a few deep breaths, relax my shoulders, and unclench my stomach and whatever else is tight in my body.
  
  2. Remind myself of the actual stakes of the situation e.g. am I going to die if this goes wrong? No. I am safe. I am loved. I matter. I am valuable. I am not a failure. I am not going to lose everything if this goes wrong.
  
  3. Usually I get to the conclusion that all I can do is try my best and even if things go horribly wrong, there's a way to fix it and I think of what that way is and find comfort in that 👍

Question: How to motivate yourself to excercise??? My health isnt good and I want to get active
Answer:
1. Don't make it a punishment for yourself in your mind or like something that you have to do or else you're a bad person lol the more pressure you put on yourself about it, the less motivation you'll have.
  
  2. Find ways to exercise that you actually like!!! I hate the gym and I hate lifting weights so instead of trying to force myself to do that I go on runs and do body weight excercises like push-ups and sit-ups bc I actually like those things! Find what is enjoyable to you.
  
  3. Start small. Don't try to run 6 miles everyday. It might feel dumb but just start out like 2 days a week doing something short and gradually build up so it feels manageable.
